The module root file runs your page. Helper files provide declarations.

### Root execution

Top-level runtime code in the module root runs as the page's implicit start function. Helper files do not run their own top-level code.

### Page fragments

Direct top-level templates in the root become page fragments:

- A const fragment (the `#` prefix form) folds at compile time and becomes static HTML.
- A runtime fragment (the plain bracket form) runs at runtime and fills a slot in the page.

### Helpers

Helper files export functions, types and constants. The root imports and uses them. Do not put page fragments in helper files.

### Remember

- Only the active root runs top-level code.
- Direct top-level templates become fragments.
- Imported roots do not replay their runtime.